cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques for face hallucination, which involves generating high-resolution face images from low-resolution inputs. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning algorithms (AI) and statistical analysis of image patches (MM), which are relevant to these sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of uncontrolled settings with large pose and illumination variations, which could fall under the graphics (GR) sub-category.
